      • parse

        public static AST parse(java.lang.String input)
                 throws ParserException
        Convenience method to tokenize and parse the given input
        Parameters:
        input - The expression to be evaluated, as a string
        Returns:
        An abstract syntax tree for that expression
        Throws:
        ParserException - if there is a parsing error

      • parseNoException

        public static AST parseNoException(java.lang.String input)
        Like parse, but it does not throw any annotated exceptions. This is to avoid repeatedly annotating tests to throw exceptions. Internally, if tokenizing or parsing input throws a ParserException, this will trigger test failure.
        Parameters:
        input - The expression to be evaluated, as a string
        Returns:
        An abstract syntax tree for that expression
